<section class="section" aria-labelledby="why">
    <p class="section-kicker">Why</p>
    <h2 id="why" class="section-title">Why this exists</h2>

    <p class="section-lead">
        The hardest part of starting is usually not the run, it’s finding reliable setup info.
    </p>

    <p>
        A lot of “getting started” knowledge lives in scattered places: Discord pins, docs, old posts,
        speedrun.com pages, videos, and guides that assume you already know the terminology.
    </p>

    <p class="hint">
        This site exists to collect the essentials in one place, written clearly and kept up to date.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="for">
    <p class="section-kicker">What you’ll find</p>
    <h2 id="for" class="section-title">What this site is for</h2>

    <ul class="callouts">
        <li><strong>Timing reference</strong> for each game (RTA vs IGT, autosplitters, common gotchas)</li>
        <li><strong>LiveSplit guidance</strong> with sensible defaults and minimal jargon</li>
        <li><strong>Downpatch steps</strong> when a category requires an older version</li>
        <li><strong>Purchase/version notes</strong> (where to buy, which storefront/version matters)</li>
        <li><strong>Links outward</strong> to the best community guides rather than duplicating them</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="hint">
        Think of it as a stable “setup index” you can link to.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="not">
    <p class="section-kicker">Boundaries</p>
    <h2 id="not" class="section-title">What this site is not</h2>

    <ul class="callouts">
        <li>Not a leaderboard</li>
        <li>Not a replacement for game communities</li>
        <li>Not a rules authority</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="hint">
        Everything here should point you towards the community, not away from it.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section" aria-labelledby="use">
    <p class="section-kicker">How it works</p>
    <h2 id="use" class="section-title">How to use it</h2>

    <p class="section-lead">If you’re new, this is the usual path:</p>

    <ol class="callouts">
        <li>Pick the game you want to run</li>
        <li>Check timing and rules basics</li>
        <li>Set up LiveSplit</li>
        <li>Follow any version or downpatch steps</li>
        <li>Move on to the game’s community guides</li>
    </ol>

    <nav aria-label="Browse">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/guide"><strong>Browse guides</strong></a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <p class="hint">
        If you already run a game, these pages should still be useful as a reference you can share.
    </p>
</section>

